# CHEKIO Component Standards - Cursor Rules

## Component Usage Standards

### 1. ALWAYS use CHEKIO prefixed components for Checkio applications:

- Use `CHEKIOButton` instead of regular `Button`
- Use `CHEKIOInput` instead of regular `Input`
- Use `CHEKIOSelect` components instead of regular `Select` components
- Use `CHEKIOTable` components instead of regular table elements
- Use `CHEKIOProgressBar` for progress indicators
- Use `CHEKIOTabs` and `CHEKIOTab` for tab navigation
- Use `CHEKIOActionButton` for action buttons (edit, delete, view)
- Use `CHEKIOModal` for modal dialogs

### 2. Import from the centralized index:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Import from centralized index
import {
  CHEKIOActionButton,
  CHEKIOButton,
  CHEKIOInput,
  CHEKIOModal,
  CHEKIOProgressBar,
  CHEKIOSelect,
  CHEKIOSelectContent,
  CHEKIOSelectItem,
  CHEKIOSelectTrigger,
  CHEKIOSelectValue,
  CHEKIOTab,
  CHEKIOTabs,
  CHEKIOTable,
  CHEKIOTableBody,
  CHEKIOTableCell,
  CHEKIOTableHead,
  CHEKIOTableHeader,
  CHEKIOTableRow,
} from "@/components";

// ❌ INCORRECT - Import individual components
import { CHEKIOButton } from "@/components/CHEKIOButton";
```

### 3. Button Variants:

- Use `variant="search"` for search buttons (blue background)
- Use `variant="refresh"` for refresh buttons (light blue background)
- Use `variant="primary"` for primary actions
- Use `variant="secondaryBlue"` for secondary actions
- Use `variant="approve"` for download Excel buttons (green background) — **ALWAYS** use green for all "Descargar Excel" / export actions

### 4. Action Button Variants:

- Use `variant="edit"` for edit buttons (orange background)
- Use `variant="delete"` for delete buttons (red background)
- Use `variant="view"` for view buttons (blue background)

### 5. Table Structure - **CRITICAL: ALWAYS USE CHEKIOTable**:

- **NEVER** use `DataTable` from `@/components/ui/table-generic` or any other table component
- **ALWAYS** use `CHEKIOTable` components for all data tables
- Use `CHEKIOTable` as the container
- Use `CHEKIOTableHeader` for the header section with `<tr>` wrapper
- Use `CHEKIOTableBody` for the body section
- Use `CHEKIOTableRow` with `index` prop for alternating row colors (required for proper styling)
- Use `CHEKIOTableHead` for header cells
- Use `CHEKIOTableCell` for data cells
- Implement manual pagination with `CHEKIOButton` and state management
- Use `CHEKIOLoading` for loading states instead of table loading props
- Show empty states with custom messages when data is empty

**Example Table Implementation:**

```typescript
{
  isLoading ? (
    <div className="flex justify-center py-8">
      <CHEKIOLoading size="lg" variant="modern" text="Cargando datos..." />
    </div>
  ) : data.length === 0 ? (
    <div className="text-center py-10">
      <p className="text-gray-600 font-medium">No se encontraron resultados</p>
    </div>
  ) : (
    <>
      <CHEKIOTable>
        <CHEKIOTableHeader>
          <tr>
            <CHEKIOTableHead>Columna 1</CHEKIOTableHead>
            <CHEKIOTableHead>Columna 2</CHEKIOTableHead>
            <CHEKIOTableHead>Acciones</CHEKIOTableHead>
          </tr>
        </CHEKIOTableHeader>
        <CHEKIOTableBody>
          {data.map((item, index) => (
            <CHEKIOTableRow key={item.id} index={index}>
              <CHEKIOTableCell>{item.field1}</CHEKIOTableCell>
              <CHEKIOTableCell>{item.field2}</CHEKIOTableCell>
              <CHEKIOTableCell>
                <CHEKIOActionButton variant="edit">
                  <Edit className="h-4 w-4" />
                </CHEKIOActionButton>
              </CHEKIOTableCell>
            </CHEKIOTableRow>
          ))}
        </CHEKIOTableBody>
      </CHEKIOTable>

      {/* Manual Pagination with Records Per Page Selector */}
      <div className="mt-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-4">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
          <div className="text-sm text-gray-600">
            Mostrando {data.length} de {totalCount} resultados
          </div>
          {/* Selector de registros por página */}
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <label className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 whitespace-nowrap">
              Registros por página:
            </label>
            <CHEKIOSelect
              value={pageSize.toString()}
              onValueChange={(value) => {
                handlePageSizeChange(parseInt(value, 10));
              }}
            >
              <CHEKIOSelectTrigger className="w-24">
                <CHEKIOSelectValue />
              </CHEKIOSelectTrigger>
              <CHEKIOSelectContent>
                <CHEKIOSelectItem value="10">10</CHEKIOSelectItem>
                <CHEKIOSelectItem value="20">20</CHEKIOSelectItem>
                <CHEKIOSelectItem value="50">50</CHEKIOSelectItem>
                <CHEKIOSelectItem value="100">100</CHEKIOSelectItem>
                <CHEKIOSelectItem value="200">200</CHEKIOSelectItem>
              </CHEKIOSelectContent>
            </CHEKIOSelect>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
          <CHEKIOButton
            variant="secondaryBlue"
            onClick={() => handlePageChange(currentPage - 1)}
            disabled={currentPage === 1}
          >
            <ChevronLeft className="h-4 w-4" />
            Anterior
          </CHEKIOButton>
          <div className="px-4 py-2 border bg-white text-sm text-gray-700">
            Página {currentPage} de {totalPages}
          </div>
          <CHEKIOButton
            variant="secondaryBlue"
            onClick={() => handlePageChange(currentPage + 1)}
            disabled={currentPage >= totalPages}
          >
            Siguiente
            <ChevronRight className="h-4 w-4" />
          </CHEKIOButton>
        </div>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}
```

### 6. Progress Bar Usage:

- Use `CHEKIOProgressBar` with `current`, `total`, and `text` props
- The component automatically handles styling and animations

### 7. Input and Select Styling:

- All CHEKIO components have consistent styling (square corners, proper colors)
- No need to add custom classes for basic styling
- Focus states are handled automatically

### 8. Color Standards:

- Header red: `#eb1d2e`
- Primary blue: `#2563eb`
- Secondary blue: `#dbeafe`
- Background gray: `#f9fafb`
- Border gray: `#d1d5db`

### 9. Layout Standards:

- Use Tailwind CSS grid system with `md:grid-cols-12`
- Use `md:col-span-*` for responsive column sizing
- Maintain consistent spacing with `gap-4` and `mb-6`

### 10. Icon Usage:

- Use Lucide React icons
- Always import icons individually: `import { Search, RefreshCw } from "lucide-react"`
- Use `h-4 w-4` for standard icon sizing

### 11. Code Organization:

- Keep data structures consistent
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Follow React best practices with proper key props and event handlers

### 12. Enum Usage Standards:

- **ALWAYS** use enums instead of string literals for better maintainability
- **NEVER** use hardcoded strings for status values, types, or configurations
- **CREATE** enums for all predefined values that could change or be reused

### 13. Pagination Standards:

- **ALWAYS** implement pagination for data tables with more than 10 items
- **USE** consistent pagination controls across all components
- **INCLUDE** pagination info showing current page and total items
- **RESET** to page 1 when applying filters or search
- **HANDLE** edge cases (empty results, single page, etc.)
- **INCLUDE** records per page selector in the same line as pagination controls
- **PLACE** the selector on the left side with "Mostrando X de Y resultados"
- **RESET** to page 1 when changing page size
- **PROVIDE** standard options: 10, 20, 50, 100, 200 records per page

**Pagination Implementation Pattern:**

```typescript
// State management
const [pagination, setPagination] = useState<PaginationFilterDto>({
  current: 1,
  pageSize: 10,
  totalPages: 1,
  totalCount: 0,
  sort: "desc",
});

// Handler for page size change
const handlePageSizeChange = useCallback((newPageSize: number) => {
  setPagination((prev) => ({
    ...prev,
    pageSize: newPageSize,
    current: 1, // Reset to first page when changing page size
  }));
}, []);

// Pagination UI
<div className="mt-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-4">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
    <div className="text-sm text-gray-600">
      Mostrando {data.length} de {paginationData.totalCount} resultados
    </div>
    {/* Selector de registros por página */}
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <label className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 whitespace-nowrap">
        Registros por página:
      </label>
      <CHEKIOSelect
        value={pagination.pageSize.toString()}
        onValueChange={(value) => {
          handlePageSizeChange(parseInt(value, 10));
        }}
      >
        <CHEKIOSelectTrigger className="w-24">
          <CHEKIOSelectValue />
        </CHEKIOSelectTrigger>
        <CHEKIOSelectContent>
          <CHEKIOSelectItem value="10">10</CHEKIOSelectItem>
          <CHEKIOSelectItem value="20">20</CHEKIOSelectItem>
          <CHEKIOSelectItem value="50">50</CHEKIOSelectItem>
          <CHEKIOSelectItem value="100">100</CHEKIOSelectItem>
          <CHEKIOSelectItem value="200">200</CHEKIOSelectItem>
        </CHEKIOSelectContent>
      </CHEKIOSelect>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <CHEKIOButton
      variant="secondaryBlue"
      onClick={() => handlePageChange(paginationData.current - 1)}
      disabled={paginationData.current === 1}
    >
      <ChevronLeft className="h-4 w-4" />
      Anterior
    </CHEKIOButton>
    <div className="px-4 py-2 border bg-white text-sm text-gray-700">
      Página {paginationData.current} de {paginationData.totalPages}
    </div>
    <CHEKIOButton
      variant="secondaryBlue"
      onClick={() => handlePageChange(paginationData.current + 1)}
      disabled={paginationData.current >= paginationData.totalPages}
    >
      Siguiente
      <ChevronRight className="h-4 w-4" />
    </CHEKIOButton>
  </div>
</div>;
```

### 14. Search and Filter Standards:

- **IMPLEMENT** real-time search with debouncing for better performance
- **PROVIDE** clear search placeholders and labels
- **SHOW** search results count and clear search functionality
- **RESET** pagination when search criteria changes
- **SUPPORT** multiple search criteria when applicable

### 15. Modal and Dialog Standards:

- **USE** CHEKIOModal for all modal dialogs
- **INCLUDE** proper modal titles and descriptions
- **IMPLEMENT** cancel and confirm actions consistently
- **VALIDATE** form inputs before allowing submission
- **HANDLE** loading states during modal operations
- **CLEAR** modal state when closing

### 16. State Management Standards:

- **USE** useState for component-level state
- **IMPLEMENT** proper state reset when components unmount
- **HANDLE** loading, error, and success states consistently
- **AVOID** unnecessary re-renders with proper dependency arrays
- **USE** meaningful state variable names

### 17. Error Handling Standards:

- **DISPLAY** user-friendly error messages
- **PROVIDE** retry mechanisms for failed operations
- **LOG** errors for debugging purposes
- **HANDLE** network errors gracefully
- **SHOW** loading states during async operations

### 17.1. Bulk Upload Retry Standards:

- **ALWAYS** implement retry functionality for bulk upload operations
- **PRESERVE** successfully processed data when errors occur
- **ALLOW** editing of failed records after processing
- **PROVIDE** a "Retry" button that only processes failed records
- **MAINTAIN** data integrity by not losing correct entries

**Implementation Pattern for Bulk Upload with Retry:**

```typescript
interface FormData {
  id?: string;
  // ... other fields
  status?: "pending" | "processing" | "success" | "error";
  error?: string;
  success?: boolean;
}

// State management
const [processing, setProcessing] = useState(false);
const [isComplete, setIsComplete] = useState(false);

// onSubmit - Initial processing
const onSubmit = async (data: FormValues) => {
  // ... validation logic
  
  setProcessing(true);
  const newData = [...data.items];
  let hasErrors = false;

  for (let i = 0; i < data.items.length; i++) {
    const item = data.items[i];
    
    newData[i] = { ...newData[i], status: "processing" };
    replace(newData);

    try {
      await createItem(item);
      newData[i] = {
        ...newData[i],
        success: true,
        status: "success",
      };
    } catch (error: any) {
      hasErrors = true;
      newData[i] = {
        ...newData[i],
        success: false,
        status: "error",
        error: error.response?.data?.message || "Error creating item",
      };
    }
    replace(newData);
  }

  setProcessing(false);
  
  // Only set isComplete to true if all items are successful
  const allSuccess = newData.every((item) => item.status === "success");
  setIsComplete(true);

  if (hasErrors) {
    toast({
      title: t("toast.processCompletedWithErrors.title"),
      description: t("toast.processCompletedWithErrors.description"),
      variant: "destructive",
    });
  } else {
    toast({
      title: t("toast.processCompletedSuccess.title"),
      description: t("toast.processCompletedSuccess.description"),
    });
    onSuccess();
  }
};

// handleRetryFailed - Retry only failed records
const handleRetryFailed = async () => {
  const allItems = watch("items");
  const failedIndices = allItems
    .map((item, index) => (item.status === "error" ? index : -1))
    .filter((index) => index !== -1);

  if (failedIndices.length === 0) {
    toast({
      title: t("toast.noFailedItems.title"),
      description: t("toast.noFailedItems.description"),
    });
    return;
  }

  // Validate failed items before retrying
  const validationErrors: string[] = [];
  failedIndices.forEach((index) => {
    const item = allItems[index];
    const error = validateItem(item);
    if (error) {
      validationErrors.push(
        `${t("toast.validationErrors.rowPrefix")} ${index + 1}: ${error}`
      );
    }
  });

  if (validationErrors.length > 0) {
    toast({
      title: t("toast.validationErrors.title"),
      description: validationErrors.join(", "),
      variant: "destructive",
    });
    return;
  }

  setProcessing(true);
  setUploadProgress(0);
  setIsComplete(false);

  const newData = [...allItems];
  let processed = 0;
  let hasErrors = false;
  const total = failedIndices.length;

  for (const index of failedIndices) {
    const item = allItems[index];

    // Reset status to processing
    newData[index] = {
      ...newData[index],
      status: "processing",
      error: undefined,
    };
    replace(newData);

    try {
      await createItem(item);
      processed++;
      setUploadProgress((processed / total) * 100);
      newData[index] = {
        ...newData[index],
        success: true,
        status: "success",
      };
    } catch (error: any) {
      hasErrors = true;
      newData[index] = {
        ...newData[index],
        success: false,
        status: "error",
        error: error.response?.data?.message || t("toast.createError"),
      };
    }
    replace(newData);
  }

  setProcessing(false);
  const allSuccess = newData.every((item) => item.status === "success");
  setIsComplete(true);

  if (hasErrors) {
    toast({
      title: t("toast.retryCompletedWithErrors.title"),
      description: t("toast.retryCompletedWithErrors.description"),
      variant: "destructive",
    });
  } else {
    if (allSuccess) {
      toast({
        title: t("toast.processCompletedSuccess.title"),
        description: t("toast.processCompletedSuccess.description"),
      });
      onSuccess();
    } else {
      toast({
        title: t("toast.retryCompletedSuccess.title"),
        description: t("toast.retryCompletedSuccess.description"),
      });
    }
  }
};

// Render buttons conditionally
<div className="flex justify-end gap-4">
  <CHEKIOButton
    type="button"
    variant="secondary"
    onClick={onClose}
    disabled={processing}
  >
    {isComplete ? t("buttons.close") : t("buttons.cancel")}
  </CHEKIOButton>
  
  {/* Show Retry button when complete and there are errors */}
  {isComplete &&
    watch("items").some((item) => item?.status === "error") && (
      <CHEKIOButton
        type="button"
        variant="primary"
        onClick={handleRetryFailed}
        disabled={processing}
      >
        {processing ? (
          <>
            <Loader2 className="h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />
            {t("buttons.processing")}
          </>
        ) : (
          <>
            <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4" />
            {t("buttons.retry")}
          </>
        )}
      </CHEKIOButton>
    )}
  
  {/* Show Process button when not complete */}
  {!isComplete && (
    <CHEKIOButton type="submit" variant="primary" disabled={processing}>
      {processing ? (
        <>
          <Loader2 className="h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />
          {t("buttons.processing")}
        </>
      ) : (
        <>
          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4" />
          {t("buttons.process")}
        </>
      )}
    </CHEKIOButton>
  )}
</div>

// Make fields editable based on status
const isEditable = status === "error" || status === "pending";
const isDisabled = status === "success" || (processing && status !== "error");

<SystemInput
  control={control}
  attribute={`items.${index}.field`}
  disabled={isDisabled}
  // ... other props
/>
```

**Key Requirements:**

1. **Status Management**: Each item must have a `status` field: `"pending" | "processing" | "success" | "error"`
2. **Data Preservation**: Never lose successfully processed data when errors occur
3. **Editable Failed Records**: Fields with `status === "error"` must remain editable after processing
4. **Disabled Success Records**: Fields with `status === "success"` must be disabled
5. **Retry Button Visibility**: Show "Retry" button only when `isComplete === true` AND there are items with `status === "error"`
6. **Validation Before Retry**: Always validate failed items before retrying
7. **Progress Tracking**: Show progress bar during retry operation
8. **Toast Notifications**: Provide appropriate feedback for retry operations

**Translation Keys Required:**

```json
{
  "buttons": {
    "retry": "Reintentar"
  },
  "toast": {
    "retryFailed": {
      "title": "Reintentar carga fallida",
      "description": "Reintentando solo los registros con errores"
    },
    "retryCompletedWithErrors": {
      "title": "Reintento completado con errores",
      "description": "Algunos registros aún tienen errores. Revise la lista."
    },
    "retryCompletedSuccess": {
      "title": "Reintento exitoso",
      "description": "Todos los registros fallidos han sido procesados correctamente"
    },
    "noFailedItems": {
      "title": "No hay registros fallidos",
      "description": "Todos los registros han sido procesados exitosamente"
    }
  }
}
```

### 18. Accessibility Standards:

- **INCLUDE** proper ARIA labels for interactive elements
- **PROVIDE** keyboard navigation support
- **USE** semantic HTML elements
- **ENSURE** sufficient color contrast
- **ADD** alt text for images and icons

### 19. Performance Standards:

- **IMPLEMENT** pagination for large datasets
- **USE** React.memo for expensive components when appropriate
- **OPTIMIZE** bundle size by importing only needed components
- **LAZY LOAD** components when beneficial
- **MINIMIZE** unnecessary API calls

### 20. Code Formatting Standards:

- **USE** consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- **FOLLOW** Prettier formatting rules
- **GROUP** imports logically (React, third-party, local)
- **USE** meaningful variable and function names
- **ADD** JSDoc comments for complex functions

### 21. Layout and Spacing Standards:

- **USE** consistent spacing with Tailwind classes (gap-4, mb-6, p-6)
- **MAINTAIN** responsive design with mobile-first approach
- **APPLY** consistent padding and margins across components
- **USE** grid system (md:grid-cols-12) for complex layouts
- **ENSURE** proper visual hierarchy with typography scales

### 22. Form and Input Standards:

- **USE** CHEKIOInput for all text inputs
- **IMPLEMENT** proper form validation with clear error messages
- **PROVIDE** helpful placeholder text and labels
- **HANDLE** form submission with loading states
- **RESET** forms after successful submission
- **VALIDATE** required fields before submission

### 23. Table and Data Display Standards:

- **USE** CHEKIOTable components for all data tables
- **IMPLEMENT** responsive table design with horizontal scroll
- **INCLUDE** proper table headers with sorting when applicable
- **SHOW** empty states with helpful messages
- **PROVIDE** action buttons with consistent styling
- **HANDLE** loading states with skeleton or spinner

### 24. Navigation and Routing Standards:

- **USE** consistent breadcrumb navigation
- **IMPLEMENT** proper tab navigation with active states
- **PROVIDE** clear navigation hierarchy
- **HANDLE** deep linking and URL state management
- **INCLUDE** back navigation where appropriate

### 25. Loading and Feedback Standards:

- **SHOW** loading states for async operations
- **USE** CHEKIOInlineLoading for inline loading states
- **PROVIDE** success feedback for completed actions
- **IMPLEMENT** error boundaries for graceful error handling
- **DISPLAY** progress indicators for long-running operations

### 26. Icon and Visual Standards:

- **USE** Lucide React icons consistently
- **MAINTAIN** consistent icon sizes (h-4 w-4 for standard, h-3 w-3 for small)
- **CHOOSE** semantically appropriate icons
- **ENSURE** icons are accessible with proper alt text
- **USE** consistent icon placement and spacing

### 27. Color and Theme Standards:

- **FOLLOW** established color palette strictly
- **USE** semantic color names (primary, secondary, success, error)
- **MAINTAIN** consistent color usage across components
- **ENSURE** proper contrast ratios for accessibility
- **APPLY** color consistently for similar actions

### 28. Component Architecture Standards:

- **KEEP** components focused on single responsibility
- **EXTRACT** reusable logic into custom hooks
- **USE** proper prop interfaces with TypeScript
- **IMPLEMENT** proper component composition
- **AVOID** prop drilling with context when appropriate

### 29. Data Fetching Standards:

- **USE** React Query or similar for server state management
- **IMPLEMENT** proper error handling for API calls
- **PROVIDE** loading states during data fetching
- **HANDLE** caching and refetching appropriately
- **IMPLEMENT** optimistic updates where beneficial

### 30. Security and Validation Standards:

- **VALIDATE** all user inputs on both client and server
- **SANITIZE** data before displaying
- **IMPLEMENT** proper authentication checks
- **USE** secure coding practices
- **HANDLE** sensitive data appropriately

### 31. Modern Design Patterns (Page Headers, Tables, Actions):

#### Page Header (Custom)
- **OPTIONAL**: Create page-specific headers in `_components/` when CHEKIOHeader does not fit.
- **Layout**: Icono de sección (40x40) en contenedor `rounded-xl bg-blue-50`, título, breadcrumbs.
- **Botón regresar**: Compacto 36x36, solo icono `ArrowLeft`, `hover:bg-gray-100`, `text-gray-500`.
- **Contenedor**: `rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm px-6 py-5`.

#### Table Header (Dynamic Client Colors)
- **COMPORTAMIENTO POR DEFECTO**: CHEKIOTableHeader aplica automáticamente el color primario del cliente con 15% de opacidad como fondo
- **COLOR DE TEXTO**: CHEKIOTableHead usa el color primario del cliente para el texto del header
- **ICONOS**: Los iconos en las columnas deben usar el color primario con 60% de opacidad (`${templateUser.primary}99`)
- **PERSONALIZACIÓN**: Si necesitas un estilo diferente, puedes sobrescribir con `className` y `style` props
- **ICONOS EN COLUMNAS**: `Hash`, `Layers`, `Smartphone`, `Building2`, `CalendarPlus`, `Clock`, `Activity` antes del texto
- **ESTILO BASE**: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider`, `px-5 py-3.5` en celdas
- **ACCESO AL TEMPLATE**: Usa `const { getTemplateUser } = useCookieSession()` y `const templateUser = getTemplateUser()` para obtener los colores del cliente

**Ejemplo de implementación con colores dinámicos:**

```typescript
import { useCookieSession } from "@/context/useCookieSession";

function MyTableComponent() {
  const { getTemplateUser } = useCookieSession();
  const templateUser = getTemplateUser();

  return (
    <CHEKIOTable>
      <CHEKIOTableHeader>
        {/* El header ya aplica automáticamente el color primario con 15% opacidad */}
        <tr>
          <CHEKIOTableHead>
            {/* El texto ya usa el color primario automáticamente */}
            <span className="flex items-center gap-2">
              <CalendarDays 
                className="h-4 w-4" 
                style={{ color: `${templateUser.primary}99` }} 
              />
              Nombre
            </span>
          </CHEKIOTableHead>
        </tr>
      </CHEKIOTableHeader>
      <CHEKIOTableBody>
        {/* ... */}
      </CHEKIOTableBody>
    </CHEKIOTable>
  );
}
```

**IMPORTANTE**: 
- Los componentes CHEKIOTableHeader y CHEKIOTableHead ya manejan automáticamente los colores del cliente
- Solo necesitas aplicar el color a los iconos con `style={{ color: '${templateUser.primary}99' }}`
- El fondo del header será automáticamente `${templateUser.primary}15` (15% opacidad)
- El texto del header será automáticamente el color primario del cliente

#### Badges de Tipo
- **MACHINE**: `Monitor` icon + `bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-700 border border-indigo-100`.
- **KIOSKO**: `Tablet` icon + `bg-violet-50 text-violet-700 border border-violet-100`.

#### Badges de Estado
- **Operativo**: `CheckCircle` + `bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700`.
- **No operativo**: `XCircle` + `bg-red-50 text-red-700`.

#### Botones de Acción (Ghost Style)
- **ALTERNATIVA** a CHEKIOActionButton: botones ghost `h-8 w-8` con iconos.
- **Editar**: `Pencil`, `text-amber-600`, `hover:bg-amber-50`.
- **Ver/QR**: `QrCode`, `text-blue-600`, `hover:bg-blue-50`.
- **Eliminar**: `Trash2`, `text-red-600`, `hover:bg-red-50`.
- **Siempre** incluir `title` y `aria-label` para accesibilidad.

#### Toolbar sobre Tabla
- **Layout**: Fila con "Agregar" a la derecha.
- **Fondo**: `bg-gray-50/50`, `border-b border-gray-200`, `px-5 py-3`.

#### Card Contenedor
- **Estilo**: `rounded-xl`, `border border-gray-200`, `bg-white`, `shadow-sm`.
- **Sin gradientes** para aspecto limpio y profesional.

#### Paginación
- **Contenedor**: `bg-gray-50`, `border-t border-gray-200`, `px-5 py-4`.
- **Indicador de página**: `rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white px-4 py-2`.

#### Estado Vacío
- **Icono**: Contenedor `w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl bg-gray-100`, icono `h-10 w-10 text-gray-400`.
- **Título**: `text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900`.
- **Descripción**: `text-sm text-gray-500`.

#### Iconos Lucide por Contexto
- Page Header: `Smartphone`, `ArrowLeft`, `ChevronRight` (breadcrumbs).
- Table: `Hash`, `Layers`, `Smartphone`, `Building2`, `CalendarPlus`, `Clock`, `Activity`
- Acciones: `Pencil`, `QrCode`, `Trash2` (o `Edit` si se usa CHEKIOActionButton).
- Paginación: `ChevronLeft`, `ChevronRight`.
- Empty: `Smartphone`, `Plus`.

#### Enum Examples:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use enums for status values
enum DocumentStatus {
  PENDING = "pending",
  PROCESSING = "processing",
  COMPLETED = "completed",
  ERROR = "error",
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Use enums for action types
enum ActionType {
  UNION = "UNION",
  AGRUPACION = "AGRUPACIÓN",
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Use enums for button variants
enum ButtonVariant {
  PRIMARY = "primary",
  SECONDARY = "secondary",
  SEARCH = "search",
  REFRESH = "refresh",
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Use enums for validation status
enum ValidationStatus {
  VALID = "valid",
  WARNING = "warning",
  ERROR = "error",
  NEUTRAL = "neutral",
}
```

#### Implementation Rules:

1. **Define enums at the top of files** or in separate `types.ts` files
2. **Use descriptive enum names** that clearly indicate their purpose
3. **Export enums** from centralized locations when used across multiple files
4. **Use enum values** in all conditional logic, form validation, and state management
5. **Replace all string literals** with enum references

#### Before/After Examples:

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT - Using string literals
if (status === "pending") {
  // logic
}
if (tipoAccion === "UNION") {
  // logic
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Using enums
if (status === DocumentStatus.PENDING) {
  // logic
}
if (tipoAccion === ActionType.UNION) {
  // logic
}
```

## Enforcement Rules

1. **NEVER** use regular shadcn/ui components in Checkio applications
2. **ALWAYS** use CHEKIO prefixed components
3. **ALWAYS** import from `@/components` index file
4. **MAINTAIN** consistent styling across all components
5. **FOLLOW** the established color palette and spacing standards
6. **USE** proper TypeScript types and interfaces
7. **KEEP** components modular and reusable
8. **ALWAYS** use enums instead of string literals for predefined values
9. **NEVER** use hardcoded strings in conditional logic or state management
10. **CREATE** centralized enums for values used across multiple components
11. **IMPLEMENT** pagination for all data tables with 10+ items
12. **INCLUDE** proper loading states for all async operations
13. **VALIDATE** all form inputs with clear error messages
14. **USE** consistent modal patterns with CHEKIOModal
15. **MAINTAIN** responsive design across all screen sizes
16. **IMPLEMENT** proper error handling with user-friendly messages
17. **FOLLOW** accessibility standards with ARIA labels
18. **USE** semantic HTML elements for better structure
19. **APPLY** consistent spacing and typography scales
20. **ENSURE** proper state management with cleanup
21. **IMPLEMENT** retry functionality for bulk upload operations
22. **PRESERVE** successfully processed data when errors occur in bulk operations
23. **ALLOW** editing of failed records after bulk processing
24. **PROVIDE** retry button that only processes failed records
25. **PREFER** modern design patterns (section 31): custom page headers with icon + breadcrumbs, neutral table headers with column icons, ghost action buttons, type/status badges, toolbar above tables

## Best Practices for Checkio Applications

### Component Development Workflow:

1. **Plan** the component structure and props interface first
2. **Define** all enums and types before implementation
3. **Implement** the component following CHEKIO standards
4. **Add** proper error handling and loading states
5. **Test** responsiveness across different screen sizes
6. **Validate** accessibility requirements
7. **Document** complex logic with comments

### Code Review Checklist:

- [ ] Uses CHEKIO components exclusively
- [ ] Implements proper pagination if needed
- [ ] Includes loading and error states
- [ ] Follows enum usage standards
- [ ] Has proper TypeScript types
- [ ] Is responsive across devices
- [ ] Includes proper accessibility features
- [ ] Has consistent spacing and styling
- [ ] Implements proper form validation
- [ ] Uses semantic HTML elements
- [ ] Implements retry functionality for bulk uploads (if applicable)
- [ ] Preserves successfully processed data when errors occur
- [ ] Allows editing of failed records after processing
- [ ] Applies modern design patterns for list pages (header with icon, neutral table, ghost actions, badges)

### Performance Optimization Guidelines:

- **IMPLEMENT** React.memo for expensive components
- **USE** useMemo and useCallback for expensive calculations
- **LAZY LOAD** components that are not immediately visible
- **OPTIMIZE** bundle size by importing only needed modules
- **IMPLEMENT** proper caching strategies for API calls
- **MINIMIZE** unnecessary re-renders

### Testing Standards:

- **WRITE** unit tests for complex business logic
- **TEST** component behavior across different states
- **VERIFY** accessibility with screen readers
- **TEST** responsive behavior on different devices
- **VALIDATE** form submissions and error handling

## Certification Documents Specific Rules

### Authentication and Security:

- **ALWAYS** check JWT authentication before rendering sensitive content
- **INCLUDE** proper error handling for authentication failures
- **IMPLEMENT** session timeout handling
- **VALIDATE** user permissions for different actions
- **PROTECT** sensitive certification data

### Data Management:

- **USE** proper DTOs for API communication
- **IMPLEMENT** optimistic updates for better UX
- **HANDLE** large datasets with proper pagination
- **CACHE** frequently accessed data appropriately
- **VALIDATE** data integrity before operations

### Certification Workflow:

- **MAINTAIN** consistent state across document operations
- **IMPLEMENT** proper undo/redo functionality where applicable
- **PROVIDE** clear feedback for document processing states
- **HANDLE** batch operations efficiently
- **TRACK** document history and changes

### Email Configuration:

- **VALIDATE** email addresses before saving
- **PROVIDE** bulk email management capabilities
- **IMPLEMENT** email template management
- **HANDLE** email sending errors gracefully
- **MAINTAIN** email configuration history

### Export and Reporting:

- **IMPLEMENT** efficient data export functionality
- **PROVIDE** multiple export formats when needed
- **HANDLE** large export operations with progress indicators
- **VALIDATE** export data integrity
- **IMPLEMENT** export scheduling for large datasets

## Example Usage Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT PATTERN with Enums
import { Search } from "lucide-react";
import {
  CHEKIOButton,
  CHEKIOInput,
  CHEKIOTable,
  CHEKIOTableBody,
  CHEKIOTableCell,
  CHEKIOTableHead,
  CHEKIOTableHeader,
  CHEKIOTableRow,
  CHEKIOProgressBar,
} from "@/components";

// Define enums for better maintainability
enum ButtonVariant {
  SEARCH = "search",
  PRIMARY = "primary",
  SECONDARY = "secondary",
}

enum DocumentStatus {
  PROCESSING = "Processing",
  COMPLETED = "Completed",
  PENDING = "Pending",
}

export default function MyComponent() {
  const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] = useState("");

  return (
    <div className="bg-gray-50 p-6">
      <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-4">
        <div className="md:col-span-6">
          <CHEKIOInput
            value={searchTerm}
            onChange={(e) => setSearchTerm(e.target.value)}
            placeholder="Search..."
          />
        </div>
        <div className="md:col-span-6">
          <CHEKIOButton variant={ButtonVariant.SEARCH}>
            <Search className="h-4 w-4" />
            Search
          </CHEKIOButton>
        </div>
      </div>

      <CHEKIOTable>
        <CHEKIOTableHeader>
          <tr>
            <CHEKIOTableHead>Name</CHEKIOTableHead>
            <CHEKIOTableHead>Progress</CHEKIOTableHead>
          </tr>
        </CHEKIOTableHeader>
        <CHEKIOTableBody>
          <CHEKIOTableRow index={0}>
            <CHEKIOTableCell>Item 1</CHEKIOTableCell>
            <CHEKIOTableCell>
              <CHEKIOProgressBar
                current={2}
                total={5}
                text={DocumentStatus.PROCESSING}
              />
            </CHEKIOTableCell>
          </CHEKIOTableRow>
        </CHEKIOTableBody>
      </CHEKIOTable>
    </div>
  );
}
```
